<paragraph id="8B9336CE003EFFEEFF3CFDBBFF3D5DC9" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFF3CFDBBFEBC5D2C" bold="true" box="[199,334,582,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to Brian Raber, friend of the first author and collector of the 
<typeStatus id="5497886C003EFFEEFA9AFDBBFF395DC9" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3366545003EFFEEFF3CFD73FB405B31" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9336CE003EFFEEFF3CFD73FB405B31" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFF3CFD73FEC95DE4" bold="true" box="[199,315,654,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFEB8FD72FE175DE4" authority="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,485,654,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raberi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFEB8FD72FE175DE4" box="[323,485,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Juninia raberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFE16FD73FDBA5DE4" bold="true" box="[493,584,654,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26B57A7003EFFEEFE16FD73FDBA5DE4" box="[493,584,654,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is provisionally included in this genus, awaiting the discovery of the male. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFEC6FD4EFE3F5D80" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[317,461,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFEC6FD4EFE3F5D80" box="[317,461,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A4B003EFFEEFE27FD4FFDAE5D80" box="[476,604,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1789]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[151,1436,181,1790]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Juninia annulifera (Kirsch, 1889). 13–16) Juninia leechi Lane, 1966, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Ventral habitus; 15) Lateral habitus; 16) Elytral carinae. 17) Female, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581640/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Figs 13–17</figureCitation>
) as follows: posterior area of vertex and area behind upper eye lobes with dense white pubescent macula (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFD8BFD2AFCF35DBC" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[624,769,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFD8BFD2AFCF35DBC" box="[624,769,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); central area of the pronotum and most of the elytra with minute yellowish pubescence (yellowish-white on the pronotum and grayish-white on the elytra, both distinctly more conspicuous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFE7DFCE2FDE75C74" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[390,533,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFE7DFCE2FDE75C74" box="[390,533,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum with two dense white pubescent maculae on each side (with a single macula from base to apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFE26FCBEFD9F5C10" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[477,621,834,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFE26FCBEFD9F5C10" box="[477,621,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); elytra with semicircular white pubescent macula close to the suture on posterior third (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFE41FC9AFDBE5CCC" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[442,588,870,896]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFE41FC9AFDBE5CCC" box="[442,588,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lateral carina (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B003EFFEEFCF1FC9BFCAC5CCD" box="[778,862,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–38" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1593,1617]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1569]" captionTargetId="figure-22@9.[151,1436,181,1569]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 33–38. Juninia raberi sp. nov. 33–37) Holotype female: 33) Dorsal habitus; 34) Ventral habitus; 35) Lateral habitus; 36) Elytral carinae; 37) Head, frontal view. 38) Paratype female, dorsal habitus (by Armando Ruiz Boyer)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581650/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) placed close to the humeral carina from the base (not close to the humeral carina (
<figureCitation id="13172A4B003EFFEEFDF6FC77FD925CE9" box="[525,608,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1789]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[151,1436,181,1790]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Juninia annulifera (Kirsch, 1889). 13–16) Juninia leechi Lane, 1966, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Ventral habitus; 15) Lateral habitus; 16) Elytral carinae. 17) Female, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581640/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFD76FC76FCEC5CE8" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[653,798,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifera">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFD76FC76FCEC5CE8" box="[653,798,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">J. annulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFC35FC76FB825CE8" authorityName="Heffern &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[974,1136,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Juninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raberi">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFC35FC76FB825CE8" box="[974,1136,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Juninia raberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D4D003EFFEEFF6CFC53FE8D5C84" baseAuthorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[151,383,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sibapipunga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="B958EADC003EFFEEFF6CFC53FE8D5C84" box="[151,383,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Sibapipunga beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A4B003EFFEEFE6BFC53FDE05C85" box="[400,530,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,382,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-136@6.[151,1436,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Sibapipunga beckeri (Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992). 21) Holotype female, dorsal habitus. 22–25) Male: 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Ventral habitus; 24) Lateral habitus; 25) Frontal tubercles. 26) Holotype female, elytral carinae (by Diego de Santana Souza)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581646/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Figs 21–26</figureCitation>
) by the longer antennae, elytra with semicircular white pubescent macula close to the suture on the posterior third (absent in 
