<figureCitation id="13172A4B003EFFEEFD0BFC0BFC9D5B5C" box="[752,879,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[201,1386,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–8) Purusia acreana Lane, 1956, holotype male: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Elytral carinae; 5) Head, frontal view; 6) Head, lateral view; 7) Scape, apical cicatrix; 8) Scape, detail. 9–11) Purusia acreana, female: 9) Head, lateral view; 10) Dorsal habitus; 11) Ventral habitus. 12) Purusiella wappesi (Martins &amp; Galileo, 2004), scape. Figure 12 by Francisco Eriberto de Lima Nascimento (MZSP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581638/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
